data.title: Viewer v8.11
data.text:
On this image:

Iivo (Ivan) Pavlovitch Ahava (Afanasjev)

February 6, 1896 – April 19, 1919 (23)

Prominent advocate for Karelian independence, participant of the First World War, Junior Unteroffizier of Imperial Russian Army, founder and Commander of the Northern Expedition of the Red Guard, one of the founders of the Murmansk Legion, an officer of the Karelian Regiment staff, Captain of the Allied Expeditionary Forces, was killed in suspicious circumstances His brother: Paavo (Pavel) Pavlovitch Ahava (Afanasjev)

June 10, 1898 – January 17, 1966 (67)

Participant of the Finnish War of Independence, the Olonets Expedition and the East Karelian uprising, Lieutenant

His father: Paavo (Pavel) Semenovich Ahava (Afanasjev)

December 7, 1872 – December 31, 1944 (72)

Karelian and Finnish merchant, a figure of national awakening of White Sea Karelia, founder and one of the leaders of the Union of White Sea Karelians
